#~ msgid ""
#~ "during a surge event: The glacier "
#~ "flows faster and reaches lower in "
#~ "the valley. In the upper parts the"
#~ " accumulation of snow does change, "
#~ "but not much (accumulation is slightly"
#~ " less since the glacier is thinner:"
#~ " a process called mass-balance / "
#~ "elevation feedback). At the same time,"
#~ " a much larger area than usual "
#~ "of the glacier is exposed to melt"
#~ " below the ELA. Therefore the glacier"
#~ " thins and looses volume, although it"
#~ " is still advancing."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgid ""
#~ "after a surge event: The glacier "
#~ "flow recovers its usual \"slow\" "
#~ "velocity. The glacier will retreat until"
#~ " it accumulated enough ice to advance"
#~ " again."
#~ msgstr ""

